0out%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20enjoyed%20exploring%20new%20places.%20The%20thought%20of%20boarding%20a%20flight%20brings%20a%20big%20smile%20to%20my%20face.%20Unlike%20many%20people%20who%20hate%20the%20idea%20of%20work%20travel%2C%20I%20enjoy%20it.%20I%20love%20checking%20into%20a%20hotel%2C%20going%20to%20the%20gym%20or%20taking%20a%20dip%20in%20the%20pool%2C%20grabbing%20a%20local%20coffee%20on%20my%20way%20to%20work%2C%20going%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalking-meetings-health-benefits-sitting-more-focused-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalking%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20exploring%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20is%20also%20an%20enthusiastic%20traveler%2C%20and%20together%2C%20we%20have%20explored%20the%20world%20far%20and%20wide.%20Since%20my%20son%20was%20born%2C%20we've%20focused%20on%20getting%20him%20used%20to%20traveling.%20We%20took%20him%20on%20a%2010-hour%20flight%20when%20he%20was%204%20months%20old%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2019%2F12%2F20%2Fhow-to-fly-with-baby-on-an-airplane.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%2030%20flights%20before%20he%20turned%202%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20have%20taken%20him%20to%20nearly%2020%20countries.%20It's%20already%20clear%20that%20the%20travel%20bug%20has%20bitten%20him%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20traveling%20with%20children%20is%20fun%2C%20I%20missed%20the%20spontaneity%20and%20the%20flexibility%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-solo-travel-woman-burnout-phd-academic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolo%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20stay%20wherever%20you%20want%2C%20eat%20what%20you%20like%2C%20and%20explore%20the%20city%20without%20worrying%20about%20pushing%20a%20stroller%2C%20managing%20bedtimes%2C%20or%20keeping%20a%20close%20watch%20on%20your%20child%20in%20an%20overcrowded%20area.%20I%20also%20loved%20how%20I%20could%20sleep%20past%206%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20packed%20working-parent%20schedule%20doesn't%20allow%20for%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-30s-best-time-to-solo-travel-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolo%20travel%20%3C%2Fa%3Eopportunities%2C%20but%20work%20trips%20are%20my%20way%20of%20relishing%20in%20something%20I%20enjoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoms%20need%20to%20stop%20feeling%20guilty%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-caregiver-father-distance-working-mom-guilt-shame-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorking%20moms%20have%20long%20suffered%20the%20guilt%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20spend%20enough%20time%20with%20their%20children.%20A%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F36097879%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGender%2520stereotypes%2520prescribe%2520mothers%252C%2520but%2Ctheir%2520work%2520over%2520their%2520family.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritish%20Psychological%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20found%20that%20gender%20stereotypes%20can%20predict%20the%20levels%20of%20guilt%20that%20working%20parents%20feel%2C%20with%20working%20mothers%20feeling%20higher%20levels%20of%20guilt%20compared%20to%20working%20fathers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20study%2C%20conducted%20by%20Pew%20Research%20in%202015%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22%23f2a6f4%5C%22%3Eattribution%3C%2Fmark%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cmark%20data-color%3D%5C%22%23f2a6f4%5C%22%3Elink%3F%3C%2Fmark%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20showed%20that%20children's%20academic%20and%20emotional%20well-being%20is%20not%20contingent%20on%20the%20time%20they%20spend%20with%20their%20mothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20working%20parent%20who%20loves%20to%20travel%2C%20the%20feeling%20is%20all%20too%20familiar.%20The%20guilt%20gets%20exacerbated%20when%20friends%20and%20family%20often%20look%20at%20me%20with%20surprise%20and%20ask%20how%20my%20child%20is%20managing%20without%20me.%20No%20one%20asks%20me%20that%20question%20when%20my%20husband%20is%20away%20on%20business%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20another%20conversation%20for%20another%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20decided%20to%20give%20my%20guilt%20structure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20adding%20more%20extra%20days%20on%20business%20trips%2C%20I%20realized%20how%20liberating%20it%20was%20to%20travel%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-every-working-mom-take-strategic-vacation-alone-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20first%20tried%20solo%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20planning%20a%20business%20trip%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20After%20a%20week%20of%20meetings%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20stayed%20for%20an%20extra%20night%20and%20treated%20myself%20to%20a%20glass%20of%20wine%20at%20the%20One%20World%20Observatory%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan.%20I%20just%20sat%20there%2C%20swirling%20my%20glass%20and%20watching%20the%20world%20go%20by.%20The%20sense%20of%20calmness%20was%20a%20feeling%20I%20rarely%20find%20as%20a%20working%20mom%2C%20and%20I%20loved%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I've%20stopped%20by%20the%20Great%20Wall%20on%20a%20trip%20to%20China%2C%20popped%20into%20the%20Metropolitan%20Museum%20of%20Art%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20spent%20a%20weekend%20exploring%20Angkor%20Wat%2C%20a%20temple%20in%20Cambodia%2C%20after%20a%20week%20of%20meetings%20in%20Singapore.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20learned%20to%20handle%20and%20even%20bounce%20back%20from%20my%20mom%20guilt%20spirals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20standing%20in%20winter%20clothes%20holding%20a%20coffee%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662738360dfb1341e9fdd121%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20guilt%20gets%20the%20best%20of%20her%2C%20the%20author%20will%20go%20for%20a%