an%20Private%20Property%20Be%20Taken%20Over%20For%20Common%20Good%3F%20Supreme%20Court%20Says...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20the%20Constitution%20intended%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bsense%20of%20social%20transformation%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%26quot%3B%20to%20say%20that%20the%20private%20property%20of%20an%20individual%20cannot%20be%20regarded%20as%20material%20resources%20of%20community%20and%20taken%20over%20by%20state%20authorities%20to%20subserve%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20good%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20observations%20were%20made%20by%20a%20nine-judge%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20examining%20whether%20privately-owned%20resources%20can%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bmaterial%20resources%20of%20the%20community%26quot%3B%2C%20when%20the%20counsel%20for%20parties%20including%20the%20Property%20Owners%20Association%20(POA)%20of%20Mumbai%20made%20vehement%20submissions%20that%20the%20private%20properties%20cannot%20be%20taken%20over%20by%20state%20authorities%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20constitutional%20schemes%20of%20Articles%2039%20(b)%20and%2031%20C%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20is%20considering%20the%20vexed%20legal%20question%20arising%20from%20the%20petitions%20whether%20private%20properties%20can%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bmaterial%20resources%20of%20the%20community%26quot%3B%20under%20Article%2039%20(b)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20of%20State%20Policy%20(DPSP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20may%20be%20a%20little%20extreme%20to%20suggest%20that%20'material%20resources%20of%20the%20community'%20only%20means%20public%20resources%20and%20we%20do%20not%20have%20their%20origin%20in%20the%20private%20property%20of%20an%20individual.%20I%20will%20tell%20you%20why%20it%20would%20be%20dangerous%20to%20take%20that%20view.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTake%20simple%20things%20like%20mines%20and%20even%20private%20forests.%20For%20instance%2C%20for%20us%20to%20say%20that%20the%20governmental%20policy%20will%20not%20apply%20to%20the%20private%20forests%20under%20Article%2039%20(b)...%20therefore%20keep%20the%20hands%20off.%20It%20will%20be%20extremely%20dangerous%20as%20a%20proposition%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20bench%20which%20also%20comprised%20justices%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%2C%20B%20V%20Nagarathna%2C%20Sudhanshu%20Dhulia%2C%20J%20B%20Pardiwala%2C%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20Rajesh%20Bindal%2C%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%20and%20Augustine%20George%20Masih.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20social%20and%20other%20prevalent%20situations%20in%20the%201950s%20when%20the%20Constitution%20was%20made%2C%20the%20bench%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Constitution%20was%20intended%20to%20bring%20about%20social%20transformation%20and%20we%20cannot%20say%20that%20Article%2039%20(b)%20has%20no%20application%20once%20the%20property%20is%20privately%20held.%26quot%3B%20It%20said%20whether%20the%20Maharashtra%20law%2C%20empowering%20authorities%20to%20take%20over%20dilapidated%20buildings%2C%20was%20valid%20or%20not%20was%20a%20completely%20different%20issue%20and%20would%20be%20decided%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20asked%20can%20it%20be%20said%20Article%2039%20(b)%20will%20have%20no%20application%20once%20properties%20are%20privately%20held%20ones%20because%20the%20society%20demands%20welfare%20measures%20and%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20redistribution%20of%20wealth%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20referred%20to%20the%20abolition%20of%20'Zamindari'%20and%20the%20purely%20capitalist%20concept%20of%20property%20also%20and%20said%20it%20attributed%20a%20sense%20of%20%26quot%3Bexclusiveness%26quot%3B%20to%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20socialist%20concept%20of%20property%20is%20the%20mirror%20image%20which%20attributes%20to%20property%2C%20a%20notion%20of%20commonality.%20Nothing%20is%20exclusive%20to%20the%20individual.%20All%20property%20is%20common%20to%20the%20community.%20That's%20the%20extreme%20socialist%20view%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20DPSPs%20have%20their%20foundation%20in%20the%20Gandhian%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20what%20is%20that%20ethos%3F%20Our%20ethos%20regards%20property%20as%20something%20which%20we%20hold%20in%20trust.%20We%20don't%20go%20as%20far%20as%20to%20adopt%20the%20socialistic%20model%20that%20there%20is%20no%20private%20property...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%2C%20you%20know%2C%20our%20concept%20of%20property%20has%20undergone%20a%20very%20different%2C%20very%20subtle%20change%20from%20either%20the%20extreme%20capitalist%20perspective%20or%20the%20extreme%20socialist%20perspective%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20we%20regard%20property%20as%20something%20of%20holding%20in%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hold%20the%20property%20because%20for%20the%20succeeding%20generations%20in%20the%20family%2C%20but%20broadly%2C%20we%20also%20hold%20that%20property%20in%20trust%20for%20the%20wider%20community.%20That's%20the%20whole%20concept%20of%20sustainable%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20property%20which%20we%20have%20today%2C%20as%20today's%20generation%2C%20we%20hold%20in%20trust%20for%20the%20future%20of%20our%20society.%20That's%20what%20you%20call%20an%20inter-generational%20equity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20observed%20that%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20distribute%20private%20properties%2C%20which%20have%20been%20considered%20as%20material%20resources%20of%20the%20community%20and%20gave%20the%20instance%20of%20nationalisation%20of%20private%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20must%20understand%20that%20Article%2039%20(b)%20has%20been%20crafted%20in%20a%20certain%20way%20in%20the%20Constitution%20because%20the%20Constitution%20was%20intended%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20social%20transformation.%20We%20shouldn't%20therefore%20go%20that%20far%20to%20say%20that%20the%20moment%20private%20property%20is%20private%20property%2C%20the%20Article%2039%20(b)%20will%20have%20no%20application%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20said%20it%20will%20also%20deal%20with%20the%20issue%20pertaining%20to%20Article%2031%20C%20which%20grants%20immunity%20to%20laws%20meant%20to%20protect%20DPSP.%20The%20observation%20was%20opposed%20by%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20not%20referred%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETushar%20Mehta%20said%20though%20the%20issue%20of%20Article%2031%20C%20was%20not%20referred%20to%20the%20nine-judge%20bench%2C%20but%2C%20he%20will%20assist%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arguments%20remained%20inconclusive%20and%20would%20resume%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%2039%20(b)%20makes%20it%20obligatory%20for%20the%20State%20to%20create%20policy%20towards%20securing%20%26quot%3Bthat%20the%20ownership%20and%20control%20of%20the%20material%20resources%20of%20the%20community%20are%20so%20distributed%20as%20best%20to%20subserve%20the%20common%20good%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2016%20petitions%20including%20the%20lead%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Mumbai-based%20POA%20was%20heard%20by%20the%20bench.%20The%20lead%20plea%20was%20filed%20by%20POA%20way%20back%20in%201992%20and%20it%20was%20referred%20thrice%20to%20larger%20benches%20of%20five%20and%20seven%20judges%20before%20being%20referred%20to%20a%20nine-judge%20bench%20on%20February%2020%2C%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713984060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F9ijrm348_supreme-court_625x300_15_Apri