%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20children%20don%E2%80%99t%20eat%20anything%20else.%20Fruits%20have%20natural%20sugars%20and%20can%20be%20used%20to%20sweeten%20porridge.%20Refined%20sugar%20is%20not%20advisable%2C%20completely%20avoid%20till%20one%2C%20and%20after%20that%2C%20you%20can%20use%20dates%20and%20jaggery%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Dr%20Gagneja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20one%20year%20of%20age%2C%20no%20sugar%20and%20salt%20should%20be%20given%20to%20babies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FSWn2XJyMGd4%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22salt%20n%20sugar%20for%20babies%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20your%20porridges%20tastier%2C%20you%20can%20add%20spices%20like%20%3Cem%3Ejeera%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20asafoetida%2C%20%3Cem%3Eelaichi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20saffron%20and%20more%3B%20or%20you%20can%20add%20fruits%20to%20sweeten%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20adults%20are%20moving%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F312870%2Fengineer-couple-quits-job-to-make-healthier-alternatives-to-traditional-ladoos-laddubox%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20salt%20and%20sugar%20diets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20why%20do%20kids%20need%20so%20much%20sugar%20and%20salt%3F%E2%80%9D%20asks%20Dr%20Amit%20Gupta%2C%20Senior%20Consultant%20Paediatrician%20%26amp%3B%20Neonatologist%20at%20the%20Motherhood%20Hospital%20in%20Noida.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20processed%20food%20contains%20a%20lot%20of%20salt%20and%20sugar%2C%20we%20must%20avoid%20that%20while%20starting%20solids.%20As%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20completely%20avoid%20it%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20okay%20to%20give%20it%20once%20in%20a%20week%20to%20older%20kids%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20one%2C%20babies%20should%20be%20given%20what%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20family%20eats%2C%20where%20subtle%20sugar%20and%20salt%20can%20be%20used%2C%20he%20adds.%20Encourage%20responsive%20eating%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20force%20feed.%20Just%20like%20we%20regulate%20our%20intake%2C%20accept%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%20as%20well%2C%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAppetite%20is%20a%20natural%20phenomenon.%20The%20idea%20of%20getting%20the%20child%20to%20eat%20the%20same%20as%20the%20family%20is%20to%20prevent%20fussy%20eaters.%20They%20should%20get%20used%20to%20everything%20one%20eats%20regularly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20baby%20is%20a%20clean%20slate%2C%20and%20will%20accept%20anything%20you%20give.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20I%20started%20cow%E2%80%99s%20milk%20for%20my%20son%20after%20he%20turned%20one%2C%20I%20did%20not%20add%20any%20sugar%20or%20sweetener%20to%20it.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20boiled%20and%20cooled%2C%20and%20he%20loves%20it%2C%20since%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know%20any%20other%20taste.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarima%20Dev%20Verman%2C%20a%20certified%20nutritionist%20and%20medical%20content%20analyst%20with%20The%20Healthy%20Indian%20Project%20(THIP)%2C%20states%20that%20if%20we%20start%20a%20baby%20on%20the%20sweetened%2C%20powdered%20baby%20food%20at%20six%20months%2C%20he%20or%20she%20won%E2%80%99t%20accept%20anything%20else%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amount%20of%20sugar%20in%20one%20serving%20of%20Cerelac%20is%20too%20much%2C%20which%20is%20not%20at%20all%20required%20by%20a%20baby.%20Sugar%20is%20addictive%2C%20leading%20to%20babies%20demanding%20only%20sweet%20foods%20then.%20You%20can%20instead%20use%20fruits%20which%20are%20naturally%20sweet%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhat%20are%20the%20important%20nutrients%20that%20a%20baby%20needs%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20baby%20needs%20a%20balanced%20diet%2C%20comprising%20all%20essential%20nutrients.%20Every%20meal%20for%20a%20baby%20must%20include%20fats%2C%20carbohydrates%20and%20protein%2C%20says%20Sanchita%20Daswani%2C%20a%20nutrition%20consultant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIron%20and%20calcium%20are%20essential%20for%20a%20baby%E2%80%99s%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC5Ql3wASvK7%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC5Ql3wASvK7%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC5Ql3wASvK7%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Sanchita%20Mahtani%20%2F%20Child%20Nutrition%20(%40sanchitadaswani)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCarbohydrates%20and%20irons%20are%20very%20important%20for%20babies%2C%20as%20are%20fats%20for%20their%20brain%20development.%20Along%20with%20this%2C%20a%20fruit%20and%20a%20vegetable%20is%20equally%20paramount.%20Include%20%3Cem%3Eghee%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20nuts%20and%20seeds%20for%20fats%3B%20millets%2C%20root%20vegetables%2C%20%3Cem%3Edal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Epoha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20pasta%20and%C2%A0%20quinoa%20for%20carbohydrates%20with%20fermented%20foods%20like%20%3Cem%3Eidli%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Edosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20curd%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20food%20our%20baby%20needs%20is%20available%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%20adds%20Dr%20Amit%20Gupta.%20After%20six%20months%2C%20a%20child%20needs%20complementary%20food%20to%20provide%20the%20required%20nutrition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20recipes%20available%20to%20replace%20store-bought%20cerelac.%20We%20should%20use%20those%20instead.%20Give%20lots%20of%20pulses%2C%20nuts%2C%20green%20vegetables%20and%20%3Cem%3Eghee%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20your%20kids.%20Non-vegetarians%20can%20include%20broths%20and%20soups%20which%20are%20also%20excellent%20for%20babies%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20rich%20source%20of%20protein%2C%20offer%20curd%2C%20eggs%20and%20paneer.%20Add%20nut%20butters%20and%20nut%20powders%20in%20porridges%2C%20dosas%2C%20fruits%20to%20ensure%20a%20complete%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEasy%20to%20make%20cereal%20mixes%20at%20home%2Fduring%20travel%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20experts%20advise%20parents%20to%20use%20millets%20%E2%80%94%20India%E2%80%99s%20superfoods%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20great%20for%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20roast%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Erava%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Epoha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eragi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20oats%20and%20other%20millets%2C%20and%20then%20powder%20them%20separately.%20Just%20mix%20with%20hot%20water%2C%20add%20a%20fruit%20if%20you%20wish%2C%20and%20an%20instant%20porridge%20is%20ready.%20They%20are%20great%20for%20travel%20too.%20You%20can%20also%20add%20mango%2C%20banana%2C%20apples%2C%20berries%20to%20sweeten%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Divisha%20Jadhwani%2C%20a%20baby%20and%20child%20nutritionist.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20good%20option%20for%20Indian%20households%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F290986%2Fhemapriya-natesan-sathumaavu-traditional-powder-for-babies-no-sugar-startup-earns-crores%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Esattu%20maavu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(multigrain)%20mix%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20of%20these%20powders%20and%20mixes%20are%20sold%20by%20homegrown%20brands%20in%20case%20one%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20at%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20snacks%2C%20you%20could%20try%20%3Cem%3Emurmuras%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emakhanas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20puffed%20%3Cem%3Erajgira%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20jowar%20puffs%2C%20ragi%20puffs%2C%20laddoos%2C%20and%20homemade%20cookies.%20All%20these%20can%20also%20be%20carried%20during%20travel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20one%20week%20travel%20meal%20plan%20by%20Divisha%20Jadhwani-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2F2-23-1713781689-150x79.jpg%